header.gameNote: BTI TIP-OFF TOURNAMENT AT CEDAR FALLS IA

article.headline: Massachusetts 90, Cal Poly-SLO 64
article.story: CEDAR FALLS, Iowa (AP) -- Ricky Harris scored 23 points to lead Massachusetts to a 90-64 win over Cal Poly on Friday in the opening game of the BTI Tipoff Tourney. The Minutemen (1-0) took control of a close game with a 24-2 run in the second half. Harris and Gary Forbes each scored six points during the run, which began when UMass was tied at 54. Three other players scored in double figures for the Minutemen, who played their first ever game in Cedar Falls. Matt Hanson and Lorenzo Keeler each scored nine points to lead Cal Poly (0-1).
